Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt and
@ground black pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake the chips on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Cut the @British chicken thighs{3} in half widthways. Add to a large #bowl{}
with the @dried rosemary{1} and a drizzle of oil. Season with salt and pepper,
then mix together.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Trim the @Brussels sprouts{200%g} and quarter through the root. Halve, peel and
thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned all over,
~{3-4%mins} each side.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the chicken is browned, pop it onto a baking tray lined with foil. Bake
the chicken on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through,
~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, place the (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat.

Lay in the @British streaky bacon{4} and fry until crispy and brown,
~{3-4%mins} on each side, then transfer to a plate lined with kitchen paper.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon
> thoroughly.

When the chicken has ~{3%mins} left, sprinkle with the cheese and return to the
oven for the remaining time until melted.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium heat and add in the sprouts, shallot
and remaining garlic. Season with salt and pepper, then stir-fry until
starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir in the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} until the vinegar has evaporated and the
sprouts are glazed, ~{30%secs}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Allow
to cook until the sprouts are tender, ~{4-5%mins}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat and stir through the @pecan nut halves{25%g}.

When the chips have a few mins left, halve the @glazed burger bun{2} and pop
them into the oven the warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

Pop the buns on your plates, then spread the @mayonnaise{2%tsp} on the bases
and the @redcurrant jelly{50%g} on the lids.

Stack each bun with the cheesy chicken thighs and bacon, then sandwich shut.

Serve the chips and glazed pecan sprouts alongside.

Enjoy!